title: Cali shreds Eco-law for Musk, fails to see irony
description:
Elon Musk is planning to build what he coolly calls his "gigafactory," a place to assemble batteries for what he thinks will be the next generation of electric cars. Five states are battling for the privilege of being home to Musk's super-cool factory, but California is willing to go the extra mile, according to their governor, by ignoring a statute designed to protect the environment. For an electric car factory. Does no one else see the irony but The Resident?
